{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos279.erdos_279 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos279.erdos_279.","id":"vf_abacbb638ef4bc69","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #279: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $k\\geq 3$. Is there a choice of congruence classes $a_p\\pmod{p}$ for every prime $p$ such that all except finitely many integers can be written as $a_p+tp$ for some prime $p$ and integer $t\\geq k$? Current best: This may be true with the primes replaced by any set $A\\subseteq \\mathbb{N}$ such that\\[\\lvert A\\cap [1,N]\\rvert \\gg N/\\log N\\]and\\[\\sum_{\\substack{n\\in A\\\\ n\\leq N}}\\frac{1}{n} -\\log\\log N\\to \\infty\\]as $N\\to \\infty$. Prize: no. Tags: covering systems, number theory, primes.","id":"vf_f407aedc44112351","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/279.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_abacbb638ef4bc69","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"erdos:279","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_abacbb638ef4bc69","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"vf_f407aedc44112351","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_f407aedc44112351","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"erdos:279","trust":"signed"}],"external_references":[],"formal_conjectures_acti